  "texts": [
    "Flips in low-cardinality categorical variables are rare under TAB-DRW.",
    "In a 5K-row table, we typically observe only around 30 such cases.2.",
    "Nearly half of the flipped samples are misclustered before watermarking, suggesting that the watermark embedding improves rather than disrupts their semantic coherence.3.",
    "Among the remaining aligned samples that flip, we find that they tend to lie close to the cluster boundary.",
    "Across the three table examples, their average distance to the boundary is 0.29, compared with 0.77 for the other samples."
